items.text: Brunch with kids

Try their nasi lemak & mee siam for brunch. For dinner, tuck into wagyu burger or grilled pork rack.  Overall great for gatherings but limited seats & pricey. Will still return cos kids+dogs friendly!
Enjoyed the pastas. Esp. the lamb ragout.
Prawn and Ham linguini is good. Never miss their homemade honey lemon as well!
There's always one of these cuties sitting here. They have to sit outside though
great for brunch and tapas for dinner!
Mee Siam and Salted Caramel cake FTW!
Brie Parma Ham Panini - simple and wonderful
Still thinking about the awesome duck confit I had here last night. So flavourful, tender and moist! My friend and I agreed that it's VERY good. Love the slightly sweet salad dressing! I'll be back💕
Do reservations if not outdoors seat are hot and cramp
Mee Siam a must have for breakfast and their house baked bread. Opens at 9AM.  CLOSED ON MONDAYS. Limited seating so try to reserve a table.
Great food, cakes are all right in flavour, straight foward, not complex.
The rainbow cake is a must try . It's beautiful and tastes as good as it's looks. Loves seating by the the window . The feel is simply nostalgic!
Take bus Route 78 from Clementi station
It's was terrific the duck confit!
Great service, average grub, terrible fries. Decent if in the area but not worth the journey. Interesting beers and wine.
Love this place. I personally think the breakfast are better than the mains. Great appetisers and decent coffee. Will sure be back again. :)
A nice homely place, decent coffee, fresh bread & the lamb ribs & chips was great!
Fluffy pancakes live up to its name - fluffiest I've had so far! Yums:D
Staff were super friendly, and happy to give recommendations of their food. Menu is reasonably priced and the ambience is pretty good for small or large group gathering.
Portobello Mushrooms - light, juicy and delicious !
Like the little touches-Little fruits tt came with my eggs Benedict which were nicely cooked. Simple decor & relaxing ambience. Has an alfresco area. Decent coffee. Wil come again to try other items!
Breakfast portions are decent, but coffee is disgustingly disappointing. Come here for just the food.
Something new to excite your pallet
Rainbow cake and peanut butter cake were not good. Dry and hard.

Take bus 285 from Clementi bus interchange to come here guys!

Cosy location with indoor/outdoor seating. Sit outdoors if you're heading there after sunset. Quite pricey w/ mains $20+ but everyone raves about the food. Coffee is average, salted caramel cake good.
Only tried the ham and prawn linguine but already left me wanting more! Ice latte was so so. Great music choices ;)
Taxi ride from clementi station was sgd5.20...used gps to guide taxi driver
the lamb ribs, oh so fine.
Duck confit and baked lamb ribs are unexpectedly good. Meat is tender. A little on the pricey side but still worth it.
so far the better cafe in the west. food is nothing to shout abou5 but the people and environment is cosy.
The waffles tasted really good, not too hard or too soft. Great Sunday spent here😊 staffs were servicing really well.
Great stuff on the breakfast menu. If you're here for the first time, try the toastie!
Great little resto-bar in the middle of nowhere.
Seated tuna and lamb ribs were really good! Rainbow cake is meh...
Friendly staff + delicious and tender lamb ribs!!
so far the better cafe in the west. food is nothing to shout about, but the people and environment is cosy.
add on bacon $4 for only 3 pieces of bacon......expansive???
There's Mee Siam & Nasi Lemak for breakfast. And I realized I can bring my pet dog & sit in the alfresco area. Love!
This service can be so wildly unpredictable. It don't matter if you're really polite with them, you just get a totally stare from them
Try the pancakes. Yes I know they are extremely heavy on the calorie count. But trust me: THEY ARE WORTH IT.

Cakes are so delightful... how could u say no to them here?!
Cheapest Egg Ben in SG @ $10. Must try their mee siam. No skim milk here so only full cream for your coffees, lattes, flat whites etcetera...
The food is so good.  Ordered a duck confit and baked lamb ribs and we were blown away. The meat were so delicious qnd tender. Worth the twenty minutes walk here from Clementi mrt. ☆☆☆☆☆
Dessert is better
Eggs Benedict at $10!!!! And is pretty yummy. Staff is Very attentive. So Long u r open to alfresco dining, u dun need wait Very Long. Rare gem. I'll b back.
The prawn and ham linguini taste wonderful except that its abit too oily.
Brunch till 3pm on weekends !
The fluffy pancakes weren't too bad and were full and thick.
Duck confit! And the prawn and ham linguine was such a simple, yet delicious dish! Even the fries were fried to perfection... :)
Average at best. Mee siam was a blend of Mee siam & laksa, in my opinion. The Nasi Lemak was a bit strange with poached egg and tomato. Cakes and bread were good though.
Guess it's popular because there are not many choices of cafés in this area. Baked lamb ribs fare better as my duck confit is only a 5 out of 10.
Eggs benedicts
Breakfast here is really awesome! Love the bread too, tastes really good and can be eaten alone or buttered.
Open Tuesday - Friday for lunch and dinner.  Opens at 9am on weekends and public holidays.  Closed Mondays.
Baked lamb ribs was good. Going back to try other stuff
The baked lamb ribs are as good as everyone says, if a little on the small side (made up for by the fries though). Crab cakes also pretty great. Lovely spot on the corner of a residential estate.
Their Spicy Prawn and Bacon Linguine was good! Long black was strong as well!
Seared tuna was amazing! Check out the lamb and duck too
Go on, order the bread basket and judge for yourself.
Bread basket is a must for bread lovers
Amazing coffee
